<img src=http://ara11.org/serial.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usanterre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Santerre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/20/02 12:19:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22895.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I think it's great except 1 problem</span><hr size=1> To the Verant folks that I am sure will read this thread:  thanks for the attempt at solving what is indeed a serious problem.  I believe there is a flaw in this approach, however.  Having a log of the sequence of combat actions is essential- when a mob starts casting, when I was healed in relation to when I was getting hit, and when and for how long I was out of range of the mob are important chronologically - and seeing my hits with them adds a real-time context to that info.  For example. think of a mob that is ENRAGED... me getting hit being in a different place as seeing the mob riposting is a bad thing - potentially fatal.  <br>
<br>
I suggest that problem was not in the presentation of combat info; the problem was that we were losing chat messages in between combat messages.<br>
<br>
I suggest that you take a different track and you move all CHAT text (say /gu /g /ooc /auc /t /chat /shout) to a seperate window (or seperate pane, a la DAoC) and leave the combat messages back where they were, just adding the filter for myhits.  I believe this solution will be far more easily understood and better received by your user base, and I suspect it will also be easier to implement.  I do respect the work you've done here, obviously this was significant effort and somebody's good idea; but it was one of those things that I could not have evaluated without actually seeing.<br>
<br>
Now that I sound like I am kissing ass, I'll stop and take my flames..  I'd just really like to see this suggested implementation go live, it would help me and many other players immensely.<br>
<br>
